# Build Plan ‚Äî Attendance Management System

## Overview

The build is split into **10 phases**, executed in dependency order.
Each phase produces a working, testable increment.

---

## Phase 1 ‚Äî Project Scaffolding

> Lay out the full directory structure and config files before writing any logic.

**Tasks:**
- Create monorepo directory layout:
  ```
  attendance-system/
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ backend/          # Clojure Ring + Compojure
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ frontend/         # ClojureScript + Shadow-cljs + Reagent
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker/           # Dockerfiles
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ scripts/          # Shell helper scripts
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ migrations/       # SQL migration files
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Makefile
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ .env.example
  ```
- Create `backend/project.clj` (Leiningen) with all dependencies:
  - `ring`, `compojure`, `ring-oauth2`, `buddy-sign` (JWT), `next.jdbc`, `hikari-cp`, `cheshire` (JSON), `clj-http`, `environ`
- Create `frontend/shadow-cljs.edn` with build targets (`:app` for dev, `:release` for prod)
- Create `frontend/package.json` for npm deps (React, ReactDOM)
- Create `.env.example` with all required env vars
- Create root `Makefile` with all targets stubbed out

**Output:** A compilable (empty) project skeleton

---

## Phase 2 ‚Äî Database Setup

> Define the complete PostgreSQL schema and migration system.

**Tasks:**
- Choose migration tool: **Flyway** (via shell script) or plain ordered `.sql` files run by `scripts/migrate.sh`
- Write migration SQL files:
  - `V1__create_users.sql`
  - `V2__create_attendance_records.sql`
  - `V3__create_leave_requests.sql`
  - `V4__create_leave_balances.sql`
  - `V5__create_work_policies.sql`
  - `V6__create_user_news_filters.sql`
  - `V7__create_api_keys.sql`
- Write `scripts/seed.sh` ‚Äî inserts a default admin user and sample employees
- Configure `docker-compose.yml` PostgreSQL service with volume for persistence

**Output:** Running PostgreSQL with full schema, seedable via `make db-seed`

---

## Phase 3 ‚Äî Backend Core

> Set up the Clojure app server, middleware stack, routing skeleton, and DB connection.

**Tasks:**
- Set up Ring + Compojure app entry point (`core.clj`)
- Configure middleware stack:
  - JSON body parsing (`ring-json`)
  - CORS headers
  - Exception handling middleware (returns structured JSON errors)
  - JWT auth middleware (validates Bearer token on protected routes)
  - Role-check middleware (`require-admin` wrapper)
- Set up database connection pool (HikariCP via `next.jdbc`)
- Define all route namespaces (stubs returning `200 OK`):
  - `routes.auth`, `routes.attendance`, `routes.leave`, `routes.users`, `routes.reports`, `routes.policy`, `routes.profile`, `routes.dashboard`
- Write `config.clj` ‚Äî reads all env vars via `environ`
- Health check endpoint: `GET /health`

**Output:** Backend server starts, all routes respond, DB connection live

---

## Phase 4 ‚Äî Authentication

> Implement Google OAuth 2.0 SSO + JWT issuance + approval flow.

**Tasks:**
- Configure `ring-oauth2` with Google provider (client ID/secret from env)
- OAuth callback handler:
  - Extract Google profile (email, name, avatar)
  - If user exists and `active` ‚Üí issue JWT
  - If user doesn't exist ‚Üí create with `pending` status ‚Üí return "awaiting approval" response
  - If user is `rejected` ‚Üí return 403
- JWT utilities (`auth/jwt.clj`):
  - `sign-token [user]` ‚Äî creates short-lived token (expires at browser-close via session cookie flag)
  - `verify-token [token]` ‚Äî validates and returns claims
- Auth middleware: attach user to request context
- Admin endpoints for approvals:
  - `GET /api/users/pending`
  - `PUT /api/users/:id/approve`
  - `PUT /api/users/:id/reject`
- Logout: `POST /auth/logout` (clears cookie)

**Output:** Full Google SSO login ‚Üí pending ‚Üí admin approval ‚Üí active access flow working

---

## Phase 5 ‚Äî Attendance API

> Core business logic: check-in/out with geofencing, records, and leave management.

**Tasks:**
- **Geofence validation** (`attendance/geo.clj`):
  - Haversine formula to compute distance between user coords and office coords
  - Check if within configured radius
- **Check-in** (`POST /api/attendance/checkin`):
  - Validate GPS coords present
  - Validate within geofence
  - Check no existing open check-in for today
  - Insert record with `check_in_time`, coords, status = `present`
- **Check-out** (`POST /api/attendance/checkout`):
  - Find today's open record
  - Update `check_out_time`, coords, compute `total_hours`
  - Apply late/half-day rules against work policy
- **Records query** (`GET /api/attendance`): own records with date range filter
- **Admin override** (`PUT /api/attendance/:id`): edit any field
- **Leave CRUD:**
  - Submit request, list own requests, admin list all, approve/reject
  - Update leave balance on approval
  - Insert approved-leave attendance record (status = `leave`)
- **Leave balance** endpoint

**Output:** Employees can check in/out, submit leaves; admin can manage all records

---

## Phase 6 ‚Äî Reports API

> Generate structured attendance/leave reports and export them.

**Tasks:**
- Report query functions (`reports/queries.clj`):
  - Aggregate attendance by date range, per employee
  - Compute: total days present/absent/late/on-leave, avg hours/day, punctuality %
  - Compute leave summary: used vs. remaining per type
- Report endpoints (all admin):
  - `GET /api/reports/daily`, `/weekly`, `/monthly`, `/range`, `/employee/:id`
- **PDF export:**
  - Use **iText** or **Apache PDFBox** via Java interop
  - Formatted table with header, rows, summary section
- **CSV export:**
  - Use `clojure.data.csv`
  - Flat row-per-record format
- `GET /api/reports/export?format=pdf|csv&type=...&from=...&to=...`

**Output:** All report types queryable and downloadable as PDF/CSV

---

## Phase 7 ‚Äî Frontend Foundation

> Set up ClojureScript app shell: routing, state management, theming, auth flow.

**Tasks:**
- Configure `shadow-cljs.edn` ‚Äî dev server on port 3000, hot reload
- App entry point (`core.cljs`) ‚Äî mounts Reagent root
- **Client-side routing** using `reitit-frontend` or `bidi`:
  - `/login` ‚Äî login page
  - `/dashboard` ‚Äî main dashboard (protected)
  - `/attendance` ‚Äî check-in/out + history (protected)
  - `/leave` ‚Äî leave requests (protected)
  - `/reports` ‚Äî reports page (admin only)
  - `/admin` ‚Äî admin panel (admin only)
  - `/profile` ‚Äî profile settings (protected)
- **State management** using Reagent `ratom` atoms + `re-frame`-lite pattern:
  - `state/auth` ‚Äî current user, token
  - `state/ui` ‚Äî theme (light/dark), loading flags
  - `state/attendance` ‚Äî today's record, history
  - `state/dashboard` ‚Äî widget data
- **Theme system** (`styles/theme.cljs` + `index.css`):
  - CSS custom properties for light and dark palettes
  - Toggle function that swaps `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`
  - Persists preference in `localStorage`
- **HTTP client** (`http/client.cljs`):
  - Wraps `js/fetch` with JWT header injection, JSON parsing, error handling
- **Auth guard** component: redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`

**Output:** Navigable shell with working theme toggle, auth protection, and API client

---

## Phase 8 ‚Äî Frontend Pages & Components

> Build every page and reusable component.

**Tasks (in order):**

### 8.1 Login Page
- "Sign in with Google" button ‚Üí redirects to `/auth/google`
- Pending approval message shown if status is `pending`

### 8.2 Dashboard Page
- Layout: top nav (logo, user avatar, theme toggle), sidebar nav, main content grid
- Widget grid (4 widget cards) ‚Äî wired to Phase 9 data

### 8.3 Check-In / Check-Out Page
- Large status card: current status (checked in / checked out)
- Prominent **Check In** / **Check Out** button
- Calls browser `navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition`
- Shows GPS accuracy, geofence validation feedback
- Today's timeline: check-in time ‚Üí check-out time ‚Üí hours worked

### 8.4 Attendance History Page
- Calendar view (month grid, color-coded by status)
- Table view below: date, check-in, check-out, hours, status
- Date range filter

### 8.5 Leave Request Page
- Form: leave type selector, date range picker, reason textarea, submit
- Table of past requests with status badges

### 8.6 Reports Page (Admin)
- Tab bar: Daily / Weekly / Monthly / Custom Range
- Date pickers per tab
- Data table with totals row
- **Export** buttons: PDF and CSV

### 8.7 Admin Panel
- Tabs: Pending Approvals | Employees | Leave Requests | Work Policy | Geofence
- Pending Approvals: list cards with Approve / Reject buttons
- Employees: table with role/status controls
- Leave Requests: table with approve/reject actions
- Work Policy form: work start time, late threshold, half-day threshold
- Geofence form: map pin input (lat/lon) + radius slider

### 8.8 Profile Page
- Display name editor
- News keyword filter manager (add/remove keyword chips)

### 8.9 Shared Components
- `<Navbar>`, `<Sidebar>`, `<Button>`, `<Badge>`, `<Modal>`, `<Table>`, `<DatePicker>`, `<Spinner>`, `<Toast>` (notification snackbar)

**Output:** All pages fully functional and wired to the backend API

---

## Phase 9 ‚Äî Dashboard Widgets

> Integrate live external data feeds into the dashboard.

**Tasks:**

### 9.1 IP Geolocation (backend)
- `GET /api/dashboard/stocks` ‚Äî server reads `X-Forwarded-For` / `CF-Connecting-IP`
- Calls free IP geo API (e.g., `ip-api.com`) to detect country
- Maps country ‚Üí exchange ‚Üí fetches indices from Yahoo Finance / Alpha Vantage

### 9.2 Stock & Commodity Widget (frontend)
- Ticker-style cards: index name, value, Œî points, Œî %, color-coded arrow
- Auto-refreshes every 5 minutes via `js/setInterval`

### 9.3 Weather Widget (backend + frontend)
- `GET /api/dashboard/weather?lat=&lon=` ‚Äî proxies Open-Meteo API
- Frontend captures browser geolocation ‚Üí sends coords ‚Üí displays result
- Shows: temperature, condition icon, humidity, wind, 3-day mini forecast

### 9.4 Tech News Widget (backend + frontend)
- `GET /api/dashboard/news` ‚Äî backend fetches from NewsAPI, filters/ranks by user's keywords
- Frontend displays headline cards: title, source, time, external link
- Keyword matches highlighted with `<mark>` styling
- Auto-refreshes every 15 minutes

**Output:** All 4 dashboard widgets live with real data

---

## Phase 10 ‚Äî Docker, Deployment & Tooling

> Package everything for production deployment.

**Tasks:**

### 10.1 Dockerfiles
- `docker/backend.Dockerfile` ‚Äî multi-stage: build uberjar with Leiningen ‚Üí run with `java -jar`
- `docker/frontend.Dockerfile` ‚Äî multi-stage: compile ClojureScript with Shadow-cljs ‚Üí serve with Nginx
- `docker/nginx.conf` ‚Äî serves frontend, proxies `/api/*` and `/auth/*` to backend

### 10.2 Docker Compose
- Services: `db` (PostgreSQL 15), `backend`, `frontend`
- Named volumes: `postgres_data`
- `.env` file for all secrets
- Health checks on all services
- `depends_on` ordering: db ‚Üí backend ‚Üí frontend

### 10.3 Makefile Targets (final)
```
make dev          # start backend REPL + shadow-cljs watch
make build        # compile frontend release + build backend uberjar
make docker-up    # docker compose up -d
make docker-down  # docker compose down
make db-migrate   # run SQL migration files
make db-seed      # seed sample data
make test         # run backend unit tests
make repl         # start Clojure REPL connected to running app
make logs         # tail docker compose logs
```

### 10.4 Shell Scripts
- `scripts/setup.sh` ‚Äî checks for Java, Node, Docker; installs npm deps; copies `.env.example` ‚Üí `.env`
- `scripts/migrate.sh` ‚Äî runs all migration `.sql` files in order against the DB
- `scripts/seed.sh` ‚Äî inserts default admin + sample employees

**Output:** `make docker-up` brings the entire system live end-to-end

---

## Build Order Summary

```
Phase 1  ‚Üí  Project Scaffolding
Phase 2  ‚Üí  Database Schema & Migrations
Phase 3  ‚Üí  Backend Server + Middleware + Routing skeleton
Phase 4  ‚Üí  Google OAuth + JWT + Approval flow
Phase 5  ‚Üí  Attendance & Leave API
Phase 6  ‚Üí  Reports API + PDF/CSV export
Phase 7  ‚Üí  Frontend Shell (routing, state, theme, HTTP client)
Phase 8  ‚Üí  All Frontend Pages & Components
Phase 9  ‚Üí  Dashboard Live Data Widgets
Phase 10 ‚Üí  Docker, Deployment, Makefile, Scripts
```

